Conclusions Lightweight RHEAs of AlxCrNbVMo (x = 0, 0.5, and 1.0) exhibiting a single BCC phase were fabricated successfully via PM. The microstructures of the bulk alloys were homogeneous, without chemical segregation, grain coarsening or micropores. A small amount of oxide inclusions was uniformly formed by in-situ reaction during the PM procedures. The alloys exhibited superior yield strength and specific yield strength compared to cast RHEAs at 25 and 1000 • C. Particularly, the Al 0 alloy exhibited an outstanding yield strength of 1513 MPa at 1000 • C.
